cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.PL. 

The paper introduces a library for model fitting in PyTorch, which is a popular deep learning framework. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the library is aimed at researchers working on deep learning or differentiable programming, which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. The library includes built-in callbacks for data visualization and logging, which are common tasks in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the library can be used for dynamic programming problems, which suggests that cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible sub-category as well.
